  <description>Plants usually hispid, rarely glabrous. Stems often branched distally, (0.15–)0.25–1(–2.2) dm. Basal leaves: petiole 1–3(–6) cm; blade oblong, ovate, or lanceolate (in outline), (3.5–)5–14(–20) cm × 20–60(–80) mm, margins lyrate, pinnatifid, pinnatisect; lobes 1–3 each side, (oblong, ovate, or lanceolate, 1.5–2.5 cm), margins usually dentate or repand, rarely pinnatifid. Cauline leaves (distal) shortly petiolate; blade (ovate or oblong-ovate, 2–4.5 cm), margins coarsely dentate, rarely subentire. Fruiting pedicels divaricate, (3–)6–12(–17) mm. Flowers: sepals (3.8–)4–7(–8) × 1–1.8 mm; petals pale yellow, (7–)8–12(–14) × (3–)4–6(–7) mm; filaments (3–)4–7(–8) mm; anthers 1.2–1.5 mm. Fruits lanceolate, (1.5–)2–4.2(–5) cm × (2–)3–5.5(–6.5) mm; valvular segment terete or slightly flattened, (0.5–)0.7–1.7(–2) cm, 2–5-seeded per locule; terminal segment ensiform, flattened, (1–)1.5–2.5(–3) cm, equal to or longer than valves, seedless; valves hispid, trichomes of 2 types (subsetiform mixed with shorter, slender ones). Seeds pale yellow to pale brown, (1.7–)2–3(–3.5) mm diam. 2n = 24.</description>
